---
description: Use for code or config touching external input, secrets, auth, permissions, command execution, templates, paths, or deserialization.
alwaysApply: false
---

Apply security-safe defaults in every task.

- Never expose or commit secrets, tokens, or credentials.
- Treat all external input as untrusted; validate and sanitize at boundaries.
- Preserve authorization and least-privilege behavior unless user-approved changes are explicit.
- Avoid unsafe execution and injection risks (command, query, path, template, or deserialization inputs).
- If a critical vulnerability is discovered, stop implementation and report it immediately.
